The mixtape
Everything in transit
Jack's Mannequin

I love this song. Everything from the lyrics to the guitar are just so great. This is the kind of song that makes you feel something.

This song is about a relationship gone sour. That is pretty obvious. But there are hints about the distance being at fault for the relationship ending. It is really unclear though. So take it with a grain of salt.

Anyways, this song leans more onto rock but not full on. More alternative really.

Isabel
Glitterbug
The wombats

Okey it's official. This band is great. This song is one of the "slow songs" of the album. And well, I like slow songs. But only when they are done well. Like She's casual and I can feel a hot one, and like those songs you don't get bored. 
Anyways. What I grasped from the lyrics were that this man met a woman named isabel. They had a one night stand. But she left the next morning. Leaving him alone when he wanted something more. 
Give it a listen. It's kind of slow but it is really good.

Cough Syrup
Young the giant
Young the giant

Jesus, is young the giant awesome i discovered this song a while back, and lete say it's a great song. 
It's absically about depression and how if you really have it there is no escape. Seeing as the narrator is sometimes "coming out" and "running to the things they said could restore him". There is plenty of references.

These guys are pretty fresh. Their sound is pretty original line the hunna or bad suns. They are great.

caption.text:
Drown - New
That's the Spirit
Bring me the horizon

Bring me the horizon is quickly becoming one of my favourite bands. Especially after the message of the whole album.

This song, the whole album actually is about depression. And ways to cope with it. In this song it's made clearer. 
Anyways. This is punk rock, so if you don't like that give it a try. I swear it"s a great song.

Savior 
Appeal to reason
Rise Against

Rise against is literally my favourite band which I feel doesn't get nearly as much recognition. And this song is one of their best. 
These lyrics have many lyrics. I like to think that it's about a man and a woman who love eachother but the relationship is not working, so they break up out of love for each other. They don't want to harm one another. But there's also the meaning that it's about nature and humans. Tbh it's up to the listener to think about the meaning.

Anyways. Great fucking band.

Tongue tied

Yet another song from grouplove, tongue tied is a great happy song, but the meaning is pretty sad.

They are about this guy who loved the girl. The guy messed up at a party and the girl got mad at him. He has a great deal of regret and is pretty sad. 
The album's name is never trust a happy song so... I think it makes sense. Great song

Colours
Never trust a happy song
Grouplove

Okey, I know group love isn't 100 percent indie. But they are pretty damn good. 
Anyways, this song os about self acceptance, you shouldn't be scared of change and should be proud of who you are. I think that's a pretty powerfull message in it's own. It's your life, live it the way you want it to, not by society's ways.

Grouplove is amazing and I am so hyped to possibly see them in november.

I can feel a hot one
Mean Everything to nothing
Manchester Orchestra

God this son is sad. Basically it's about this car crash, he crashed with his pregnant wife. She had died but he didn't want to admit it. So he stepped out and started crying on the pavement. Ambulamces started arriving and they took his wife. Then it's implied he died in the verse of the child crying in her stomach. But I think his children also died, hence why he is crying

In reality though, in an interview they admitted it's only a dream so... Anyways, this son is sad and the chords go perfectly with the voice. It really is a song about tragedy.

Cardiac Aerrest

Okey the sing talks about a relationship. It can mean many things but it is definetly a relationship.
One of the thinga I read was that it talks about an abusive relationship. Or a relationship that just lost it's spark.

Uncruel
Uncruel
House of Lions

First, sorry for the post being so late, busy day lol.

Anyways. I love this song. The way it build up to the end the "uncruel" part. Jesus it's great. The guitar, the drums, the vocals. Everything. I also get a kings of leon vibe.

Anyways. I think the lyrics are about an abusive relationship (physical or emotional.) and the guy is caught off guard when she suddenly is nice. "Not like you to be uncruel." is the prime example for this. 
Anyways. I discovered this song in my discover weekly. Great fucking song.

Rebel Hearts
The Shelters
The Shelters

Okey first this band is pretty awesome. Thats all. I love their kind of old school style. The  album art is goregeous.

The lyrics are about a girl who rises up and fights. She is on her own and is a "rebel" at least that's what I got about it. 
Seriously this song reminds me of the old school rock and roll songs. It's great.

Fluorescent Adolescent
Fluorescent Adolescent
Artic monkeys

Artic monkeys is great. But this song is especially appealing. Precisley because it's about people getting old. The excitement of the younger days are over. You are no longer in your early 20's.

Carried away
Antics
Dionysia

Carried away... This song has just been discovered. And its fucking great. It's oretty slow yet at the same time it builds tension. It reminds me of thr newest album by manchester orchestra in that sense. 
Don't Overthink it! That's pretty much the lyrics. Set your sight and aim for it. Don't overthink it just do it. Pretty powerfull mesage in the ahe where most songs are about relationships.

Run for cover
Run for cover

Guys, this is it this is the killers. Their sound is this. Like sam's town and Day and Age. It's fucking great.

The lyrics are about breakup, mostly about the post breakup. The lyrics seem to signify that they break up many times. The girl always coming back. But this time it's for real and he knows it. It became a bad thought in his head. A person he now hates.

caption.text:
Blank you out
Blank you out
SEAFRET

This song is great. 
The lyrics talk about this couple that went through a harsh breakup. The narrator is trying to "blank her out" (forget her) but he can't. He's heartbroken. Everything he sees remimds him of her. When he's alone all he thinks is about her. 
Now the song itself is kind of slow. But at the same time very soft rock? Idk it's hard to explain. Give this song a listen (Btw I'm currently listening to brand new's mew album. Tbh it's kind of meh. Have to finish it.)

For the First Time
Science & Faith
The Script

This song was a big part of my childhood. Anyways it's about this couple who are going through a rough patch, both are heartbroken and struggling with their circumstances. So they sat down to have an evening for themeselves and started talking and fell back in love.

Tbh I love the script and this whole album is great but this song is one of the better ones. Check this band out. Especially songs like breakeven and man who csn't be moved.

Give me a try
Glitterbug
The Wombats

The wombats have this great almost futuristic like sound. I can't quite put my finger on it. But it is different. And I like it. 
Anyways. The lyrics.
I think they talk about this guy wanting to get into a relationship with a girl. The girl is not so on board. But he is trying to convince her. Therefore "Give me a try" and "this could be a drug that doesn't bite." This paralels other songs that talk about the breakup. This talks about the begining of a relationship.
Anyways I love the sound of this song. It is different. But it is extremely good.

The boy who blocked his own shot
Deja Entendu
Brand New

Okey, first of all I am super hyped for their new album, I hear it's great (better be after the almost 10 year wait.) Now this guy is a lyrical genius. Almost every line can be interpreted differently. But the meaning is still the same. A guy messed up, he feels extremely guilty about it. The girl forgave him, but she still feels betrayed for what he did. She doesn't know what to do with the relationship. "Call it quits or get a grip, you said you wanted a solution you just wanted to be missed." To be honest I could go all day about the lyrics. Brand New is awesome. You won't regret listening to this song.

Dancing on Quicksand
Language and Perspective
Bad Suns

This song sounds like the narrator is telling us he messed up one too many times. Now he doesn't really have the trust of the partner and is "Dancing on Quicksand" ie: he messes up once more and it is over.

Now, this song has a great guitar. (You'll know it) and the singer has an amazing voice. Great song.

caption.text:
Bully For You
DIVORCE
JPNSGRLS

Ok I think this band is my favourite, this song is about feminism. Feminism through the ages. For example "if only she was born a son then maybe she'd still have a head." talks about the beheading of marie antonniete. It holds a positive view om feminism without being "up in your face". That's pretty much it for the lyrics.

This might very well be their best song yet. And that is something considering circulation was the greatest album.

Free to Breathe
La Divine
Cold War Kids.

I know I post way too mich Cold War Kids but they are just that good. Really you have to listen to these guys. Anyways I think this song is pretty explicit. It's about war and whats wrong with it, it's spoils. Death, destruction. And eventually they blame god for the death. Either that or a person close to them died. And the song is about mourning. This is more on the acoustic side. Very slow but great song nonetheless.

1901
Wolfgang Amadeus Phoenix
Phoenix

Had to google this song, lyrics are pretty wierd. Phoenix said that this song is about 19th century paris (Eiffel Tower etc.) but the lyrics don't really match up. What I think is happening is a couple on the verge of breaking up, the man (who we see telling the story) is fading in and out of the realtionship, he knows the "Futures Sorted Out" and doesn't care, he knows they are breaking up. Just like paris, they built the eiffel tower, then it became a tourist atraction. They are now stuck in the past. 
Great song, even better lyrics.

Run or Hide
Drinking From a Salt Pond
Run River North.

To be honest this song just means what it means. A man afraid, runing and hiding from someone abusive or his demons. That I didn't understand very well. Eventually he stands up for himself and stops runing or hiding ("I won't run or hide") and faces whatever it is he is hiding from.

Aside from the lyrics this almost verges on rock though not quite. The song itself is pretty good.

You found me
The Fray
The Fray "You Found Me" is a song about faith and the many many let downs of life. The singer is losing his faith in god because everything has been going bad in his life. He is bling god for everything that is happening to him. For not helping him when he asked ("I've been calling for years and you never left me no messages, never sent me no letters.") all around a pretty powerfull song. And a great one, sure it's a little old but it is pretty good.

First
Hold My Home
Cold War Kids

Another great song by cold war kids. 
First is a song about a couple with trust issues, although this songs makes us feel a personal connection because of the way it is narrated. It helps us really feel what they are feeling. Having you Significant Other go to a bar, or a concert without you when you don't trust them. And you getting angry at them. Lyrics aside though the melody is great (what can you expect from Cold War Kids?) and this song has more of a serious tone. Great song, great band.

Miracle Mile
Dear Miss Lonelyhearts
Cold War Kids

Another great song by cold war kids. The lyrics are basically about following your dreams. It doesn't matter if they don't net you enough money, as long as you like what you are doing. As in "I'll be alright if I can just see you." this basically means that everything will be alright if he can see the thing he loves. In this case his dreams. But appart from the lyrics the melody and the motivation put into this song is outstanding, and you can hear it in the way he sings. Great song. Great band.

Dive
Coast Modern
Coast Modern

This song is just so fun to listen to. Its got this happy feeling. Especially the chorus. A song about a happy couple in love. Honestly it makes me feel good just by listening to it. The melody is great. The lyrics are also great. Just an all around good song.

Can We Hang On?
La Divine
Cold War Kids

In reality most of this album is pretty good, but this is one of the best. The lyrics talk about a relationship, possibly being doomed at the end. They are trying their best to make it together as seen in "I'll think about tommorrow if I can get through tonight. I know that we'll be alright. Can we be strong?" This song is really good with meaningfull lyrics (like most of cold war kids songs) definetly check it out.

Circulation: JPNSGRLS

Man, this album is an all time favourite of mine, it leans more onto punk rock tan alt (especially david and goliath) but don't let that discourage you. There are more docile songs, such as "Souther Comforting" and "Tennis Shoes". This is definetly a do not miss if you like well thought lyrics (listen to brandon and then google brandon teena). Circulation is also a magnificent song.

caption.text:
100: The Hunna.

With it's debut last year the hunna's first album titled "100" is a great way to show what this band is made of. Starting with songs like "bonfire" or "She's Casual", every song portrays some meaning of the band and excels in fun factor. Make sure to not miss the acoustic versions!

A black mile to the Surface: Manchester Orchestra.

A black mile to the surface is quite possibly one of the best album's this year. From the Maze to the silence every single song tells a story about a family in a town. From the miners in "the gold" to the car crash in "the wolf" even to the heartwarming love story of "the parts" and especially the gutwrentching "the silence". Having a wide variety of styles yet not strafing too far from their own style, this is a must have for every music lover.
